<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2006-10-20T12:16:40-07:00</updated>
<published>2006-10-20T12:16:40-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2303&amp;p=18686#p18686</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2303&amp;p=18686#p18686"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[If I were rich...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2303&amp;p=18686#p18686"><![CDATA[
There are problems with making and selling games for famiclones:<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>It's hard to find famiclones in many parts of the United States. </li><li>It's harder to find famiclones that aren't bundled with flagrantly pirated software. Famiclones are legal as of 2005 when Nintendo's and Ricoh's 20-year patents run out, but copyrights on Nintendo software will outlive you. </li><li>It's harder to find famiclones without major compatibility problems, such as timing errors (hurts Rare games), incorrect fetch sequences (hurts MMC5), incorrect APU pulse duty cycle, and the like. </li><li>It's harder to find famiclones with a responsive controller. </li></ol>There are also problems with making and selling games for modern consoles: <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Console makers use a digital signature to restrict what programs their consoles can run, and a license isn't available to small companies. </li></ol>There are also problems with making and selling games for PCs: <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>The market is saturated. </li><li>Virtually no PC game players have multiple joypads and a TV-out, which are necessary for "party" style multiplayer games. </li></ol>There are also problems with making and selling games for smart phones: <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>The market is saturated. </li><li>Mobile phone D-pads tend to be unresponsive. </li><li>Many network operators use a digital signature to restrict what programs their phones can run, and a license isn't available to small companies. </li></ol><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Oct 20, 2006 12:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
